  "prompt": "What is the validity period of Non-Creamy OBC certificate?",
  "response": "The validity period of a Non-Creamy Layer Other Backward Class (OBC) certificate can vary depending on the specific guidelines and regulations of the issuing state or institution. Generally, the certificate is valid for one financial year and needs to be renewed annually to account for any changes in the applicant's income status. Applicants should check with the specific authority or institution requiring the certificate to confirm the exact validity period and renewal process.",
